net.received.rate.maximum.kiloBitsPerSec.helpText: Maximum network data receive rate over five minute windows.

datastore.numberWriteAveraged.rate.avera.helpText: Average write IOPS sent from this host to all of its connected datastores.

net.broadcastByRx.ratio.compute.percent.helpText: Ratio of received broadcast packets to received packets expressed as percent.

mem.consumed.absolute.average.kiloBytes.helpText: Amount of memory consumed by a virtual machine, host, or cluster. Amount of machine memory used on the host. Consumed memory includes memory used by the Service Console, the VMkernel, vSphere services, plus the total consumed metrics for all running virtual machines.   host consumed memory = total host memory - free host memory.

disk.kernelLatency.absolute.average.mill.helpText: Average amount of time, in milliseconds, spent by VMkernel processing each SCSI command.

flow.rawRecordReporterWrongCollector.del.helpText: Number of raw flow records dropped as these were reported on wrong type of vRNI Collector

net.packetDropRx.ratio.compute.percent.helpText: Average ratio of dropped rx packets to total rx packets on the physical nics.

mem.overhead.absolute.average.kiloBytes.helpText: Amount of machine memory allocated to a virtual machine beyond its reserved amount. Total of all overhead metrics for powered-on virtual machines, plus the overhead of running vSphere services on the host.

net.multicastRx.delta.summation.number.helpText: Number of multicast packets received during the sampling interval.

net.packetDrop.ratio.compute.percent.helpText: Average ratio of total dropped packets to total number packets.

datastore.numberReadAveraged.rate.averag.helpText: Average read IOPS sent from this host to all of its connected datastores.

cpu.wait.delta.summation.millisecond.helpText: CPU time spent in wait state. The wait total includes time spent the CPU Idle, CPU Swap Wait, and CPU I/O Wait states.

mem.swapinRate.rate.average.kiloBytesPer.helpText: Rate at which memory is swapped from disk into active memory during the interval. This counter applies to virtual machines and is generally more useful than the swapin counter to determine if the virtual machine is running slow due to swapping, especially when looking at real-time statistics.

net.broadcastTx.delta.summation.number.helpText: Number of broadcast packets transmitted during the sampling interval.

mem.state.absolute.latest.number.helpText: One of four threshold levels representing the percentage of free memory on the host. The counter value determines swapping and ballooning behavior for memory reclamation.  0 (high) Free memory >= 6% of machine memory minus Service Console memory.  1 (soft) 4%  2 (hard) 2%  3 (low) 1% 0 (high) and 1 (soft): Swapping is favored over ballooning.  2 (hard) and 3 (low): Ballooning is favored over swapping.

flow.fiveTupleIncompleteTcp.delta.summat.helpText: Number of Five Tuples dropped due to incomplete tcp flags

disk.queueLatency.absolute.average.milli.helpText: Average amount of time spent in the VMkernel queue, per SCSI command, during the collection interval.

net.usage.delta.summation.kiloBytes.helpText: Network utilization (combined transmit- and receive-rates) during the interval. Sum of data transmitted and received across all physical NIC instances connected to the host.

mem.swapoutRate.rate.average.kiloBytesPe.helpText: Rate at which memory is being swapped from active memory to disk during the current interval. This counter applies to virtual machines and is generally more useful than the swapout counter to determine if the virtual machine is running slow due to swapping, especially when looking at real-time statistics.

net.usage.rate.maximum.kiloBitsPerSecond.helpText: Maximum total network usage rate over five minute windows.

net.packetsTx.delta.summation.number.helpText: Number of packets transmitted during the interval. Number of packets transmitted across each physical NIC instance on the host.

disk.totalLatency.absolute.average.milli.helpText: Average amount of time taken during the collection interval to process a SCSI command issued by the Guest OS to the virtual machine. The sum of kernelLatency and deviceLatency.

disk.busResets.delta.summation.number.helpText: Number of SCSI-bus reset commands issued during the collection interval.

cpu.usagemhz.rate.average.megaHertz.helpText: CPU usage, as measured in megahertz, during the interval. Sum of the actively used CPU of all powered on virtual machines on a host. The maximum possible value is the frequency of the processors multiplied by the number of processors. For example, if you have a host with four 2GHz CPUs running a virtual machine that is using 4000MHz, the host is using two CPUs completely. 4000 / (4 x 2000) = 0.50

mem.usage.absolute.average.percent.helpText: Memory usage as percentage of total configured or available memory, expressed as a hundredth of a percent (1 = 0.01%). A value between 0 and 10,000. Percentage of available machine memory:   consumed ÷ machine-memory-size

mem.active.absolute.average.kiloBytes.helpText: Amount of memory that is actively used, as estimated by VMkernel based on recently touched memory pages. Sum of all active metrics for all powered-on virtual machines plus vSphere services (such as COS, vpxa) on the host.

cpu.costop.delta.summation.millisecond.helpText: Time spent in Co-Stop state by all the VMs of this host.

net.droppedTx.delta.summation.number.helpText: Number of transmit packets dropped during the collection interval.

net.packetDropTx.ratio.compute.percent.helpText: Average ratio of dropped tx packets to total tx packets on the physical nics.

net.broadcastByTx.ratio.compute.percent.helpText: Ratio of transmitted broadcast packets to transmitted packets expressed as percent.

cpu.run.delta.summation.millisecond.helpText: Time spent in RUN state by all the VMs of this host.

net.transmitted.rate.maximum.kiloBitsPer.helpText: Maximum network data transmit rate over five minute windows.

cpu.ready.delta.summation.millisecond.helpText: Percentage of time that the virtual machine was ready, but could not get scheduled to run on the physical CPU. CPU ready time is dependent on the number of virtual machines on the host and their CPU loads.

net.packetsRx.delta.summation.number.helpText: Number of packets received during the interval. Total number of packets received on all virtual machines running on the host.

net.received.rate.average.kiloBitsPerSec.helpText: Average rate at which data was received during the interval. This represents the bandwidth of the network. The rate at which data is received across each physical NIC instance on the host.

disk.deviceLatency.absolute.average.mill.helpText: Average amount of time, in milliseconds, to complete a SCSI command from the physical device.

net.packetDrop.ratio.maximum.percent.helpText: Maximum 5 min interval ratio of total dropped packets to total number packets.

net.droppedTotal.delta.maximum.number.helpText: Maximum number of dropped packets over any 5 min interval in the selected duration (rx + tx).

net.transmitted.rate.average.kiloBitsPer.helpText: Average rate at which data was transmitted during the interval. This represents the bandwidth of the network. The rate at which data is transmitted across each physical NIC instance on the host.

net.usage.rate.average.kiloBitsPerSecond.helpText: Network utilization (combined transmit- and receive-rates) during the interval. Sum of data transmitted and received across all physical NIC instances connected to the host.

sys.uptime.absolute.latest.second.helpText: Total time elapsed, in seconds, since last system startup.

disk.commandsAborted.delta.summation.num.helpText: Number of SCSI commands aborted during the collection interval.

net.droppedRx.delta.summation.number.helpText: Number of receive packets dropped during the collection interval.

datastore.numberRWAveraged.rate.average..helpText: Average total IOPS sent from this host to all of its connected datastores.

mem.reservedCapacity.absolute.average.me.helpText: Total amount of memory reservation used by powered-on virtual machines and vSphere services on the host. Includes overhead amount.

cpu.usage.rate.average.percent.helpText: CPU usage as a percentage during the interval. Actively used CPU of the host, as a percentage of the total available CPU. Active CPU is approximately equal to the ratio of the used CPU to the available CPU.   available CPU = # of physical CPUs x clock rate   100% represents all CPUs on the host. For example, if a four-CPU host is running a virtual machine with two CPUs, and the usage is 50%, the host is using two CPUs completely.

mem.vmmemctl.absolute.average.kiloBytes.helpText: Amount of memory allocated by the virtual machine memory control driver (vmmemctl), which is installed with VMware Tools. It is a VMware exclusive memory-management driver that controls ballooning. The sum of all vmmemctl values for all powered-on virtual machines, plus vSphere services on the host. If the balloon target value is greater than the balloon value, the VMkernel inflates the balloon, causing more virtual machine memory to be reclaimed. If the balloon target value is less than the balloon value, the VMkernel deflates the balloon, which allows the virtual machine to consume additional memory if needed. Virtual machines initiate memory reallocation. Therefore, it is possible to have a balloon target value of 0 and balloon value greater than 0.

mem.swapused.absolute.average.kiloBytes.helpText: Amount of memory that is used by swap. Sum of memory swapped of all powered on VMs and vSphere services on the host.

flow.fiveTupleExpireOutbound.delta.summa.helpText: Number of Five Tuples dropped due to outbound limit hit for Source IP Addresses in Flows

net.multicastTx.delta.summation.number.helpText: Number of multicast packets transmitted during the sampling interval.

net.packetsTotal.delta.summation.number.helpText: Total number of received plus transmitted packets to received packets expressed as percent.

net.broadcastRx.delta.summation.number.helpText: Number of broadcast packets received during the sampling interval.

cluster.helpText: Name of the cluster under which the host resides.

vmknics.virtualNicParent.numberednetwork.helpText: Shows hosts virtual NICs connections type, i.e. whether full or half duplex.

maintenanceMode.helpText: Shows the maintenance state of the host, i.e. whether the host is in maintenance mode or not.

vmknics.vlan.start.helpText: Start vlan ID for the virtual NICs of a host.

vmknics.virtualNicParent.numberednetwork.helpText: IP addresses of the hosts virtual NICs in CIDR format.

manager.name.helpText: Manager, e.g. vCenter Server for VMware entities.

associatedBladeServer.helpText: Blade server associated with the host.

associatedBladeServer.name.helpText: Name of the blade server associated with the host.

manager.helpText: Shows manager associated with the host.

vmknics.virtualNicParent.numberednetwork.helpText: IP addresses of the hosts virtual NICs.

vendorId.helpText: Vendor Id for Entity - as it is referred to in the owning system e.g. MOR references in VC

vmknics.virtualNicParent.numberednetwork.helpText: IDs of the hosts virtual NICs.
MTU of the hosts virtual NICs.

vmknics.nicType.helpText: Type of virtual NICs in the host.

firewallStatus.helpText: Shows the hosts firewall status, i.e. firewall enabled or disabled.

serverdataParent.osFullName.helpText: Operating system full name installed on the host.

vmknics.virtualNicParent.numberednetwork.helpText: Interface name of the hosts virtual NICs.
Connection state of hosts virtual NICs.
Link speed of the hosts virtual NICs in Mb.

vmknics.vlan.end.helpText: End vlan ID for the virtual NICs of a host.

serverdataParent.cpuSockets.helpText: Number of CPU Sockets in a host.

serverdataParent.numCpus.helpText: Number of CPU Cores in a host.

numPnics.helpText: Number of physical NICs connected to the host.

vmknics.virtualNicParent.numberednetwork.helpText: Administrative Statuses of the hosts virtual NICs.

serverdataParent.oSHostName.helpText: Operating system running on the host.

serverdataParent.memoryMB.helpText: Physical memory of the host in MB.

vmknics.virtualNicParent.numberednetwork.helpText: Prefix length of the hosts virtual NICs.
Network address of the hosts virtual NICs.
Netmask of the hosts virtual NICs.
